main event: A sighting report indicates an observation of 11 or 12 unidentified aerial objects in Columbus, Ohio.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on March 25, 1954, at 11:45 A.M.,The observer estimated the sighting duration to be about 2 minutes,The sky was reported as bright daylight during the observation,The objects were last seen moving in a northeast direction,There was no physical evidence or photographs available for this sighting.
witness description: Details of the witness are redacted in the report.
